    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrots </strong>at an angle</p><p>Add the<strong> sliced carrot</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!), drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season them with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> sausages</strong> to the tray[s] and put everything in the oven and cook for 20-25 min, turning once halfway or until the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cumberland-sausages-and-mash-with-caramelised-onion-gravy-with-dessert/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the carrot and sausages are cooking, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium- low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and cook for 8 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cumberland-sausages-and-mash-with-caramelised-onion-gravy-with-dessert/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add<strong> </strong>the<strong> chopped potatoes </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cumberland-sausages-and-mash-with-caramelised-onion-gravy-with-dessert/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, reboil a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>gravy base</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and whisk thoroughly \u2013 this is your<strong> gravy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cumberland-sausages-and-mash-with-caramelised-onion-gravy-with-dessert/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has caramelised, add 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the<strong> gravy stock </strong>with a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong>, then increase the heat to medium and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>caramelised onion gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cumberland-sausages-and-mash-with-caramelised-onion-gravy-with-dessert/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is nearly ready, reboil a kettle</p><p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cumberland-sausages-and-mash-with-caramelised-onion-gravy-with-dessert/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cumberland-sausages-and-mash-with-caramelised-onion-gravy-with-dessert/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sausages</strong> over the <strong>mash</strong> with the <strong>roast carrot</strong> and <strong>peas </strong>to the side</p><p>Pour the <strong>caramelised onion gravy </strong>over</p><p>Enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Loved this recipe? Keep an eye out for it on the Everyday Favourites section of our menu.</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
